WEBVTT

00:55.263 --> 00:56.431
What are you doing there?

00:56.931 --> 00:58.892
I came to see if you were okay.

00:59.267 --> 01:00.310
You should've called.

01:00.977 --> 01:02.437
Did you see my letter?

01:03.229 --> 01:04.272
Yeah, I did.

01:05.315 --> 01:07.400
You saw it and didn't even call?

01:07.859 --> 01:09.110
Who is that?

01:09.652 --> 01:10.612
Mister.

01:11.237 --> 01:14.240
You said my life would reset
once I got married.

01:15.366 --> 01:17.535
That my future would change, didn't you?

01:18.119 --> 01:18.953
I did.

01:21.831 --> 01:27.045
I think my future has become more twisted
than it was.

01:27.629 --> 01:28.463
Hey.

01:29.380 --> 01:31.382
Just put the future aside.

01:31.925 --> 01:33.676
Focus on the present.

01:34.344 --> 01:36.346
"The future will take care of itself."

01:36.846 --> 01:39.766
Is that kind of thinking
focusing on the present?

01:46.231 --> 01:47.065
Hey,

01:47.482 --> 01:50.443
I'll call you tomorrow. Go home.

01:50.527 --> 01:51.986
-I'm going.
-Why?

01:52.487 --> 01:53.738
Are you running away?

01:54.322 --> 01:55.156
Mister!

01:56.866 --> 01:58.618
What's this? This is really weird.

01:59.410 --> 02:00.495
Where are you going?

02:07.043 --> 02:09.003
Come on! Why are you doing this?

02:09.546 --> 02:12.257
Why are you avoiding me like this?

02:13.675 --> 02:15.510
Would you please tell me?

02:19.305 --> 02:20.223
Mister.

02:21.599 --> 02:23.893
-You saw something in the future?
-Hey.

02:25.937 --> 02:29.732
Do you think it's a blessing
that we get to know the future?

02:42.412 --> 02:44.914
It would be terrifying not to know.

02:46.416 --> 02:49.085
What if we're destroying today
for the sake of tomorrow?

02:49.961 --> 02:54.090
What if we're complicating our fate
to change the future?

02:57.051 --> 02:58.553
I'm getting very confused.

03:00.263 --> 03:01.431
I told you.

03:02.515 --> 03:04.350
I'm going to disappear this winter.

03:05.393 --> 03:08.146
I don't know if I'm going to be alive
in two years or not.

03:13.443 --> 03:15.528
Is it a blessing to know the future?

03:16.446 --> 03:18.364
It's a complete relief!

03:18.990 --> 03:21.743
Because I get to know how screwed up
my future will be.

03:21.826 --> 03:25.205
The more you try to know,
you make it worse for both of you.

03:27.457 --> 03:28.333
What?

03:29.334 --> 03:30.418
What I meant was...

03:30.919 --> 03:32.712
So... So-joon,

03:33.213 --> 03:35.131
just trust me.

03:35.548 --> 03:38.927
Quit going to the future
for just one month, okay?

03:40.887 --> 03:43.181
You have to trust me.

03:44.057 --> 03:45.725
Whatever you see in the future,

03:46.100 --> 03:49.604
no matter how strangely I behave...

03:50.605 --> 03:52.607
I'm on your side.

03:53.233 --> 03:56.611
You have to trust that until the very end.

03:57.445 --> 03:58.321
Okay?

04:04.494 --> 04:05.370
You should leave.

04:06.204 --> 04:08.164
How can I trust you, Mister?

04:09.040 --> 04:11.334
I have no idea what you think.
How can I trust you?

04:13.253 --> 04:16.881
I won't ask for your help again.

04:19.259 --> 04:20.551
Do you really think...

04:22.971 --> 04:24.764
I wouldn't be able to protect my girl?

04:27.183 --> 04:28.726
I mean... So-joon.

04:29.769 --> 04:30.812
So-- So-joon.

04:56.212 --> 04:58.089
<i>What was that expression?</i>

04:59.590 --> 05:03.261
<i>He was a stranger.</i>
<i>I've never seen that face before.</i>

05:04.178 --> 05:06.597
<i>An unfamiliar face that I don't know.</i>

05:14.564 --> 05:15.523
Where did you go?

05:16.983 --> 05:20.028
I just went to get some air.

05:21.487 --> 05:22.322
Alone?

05:23.239 --> 05:24.115
Yes.

05:28.328 --> 05:29.787
Don't you have anything to say?

05:30.913 --> 05:32.915
You told me not to speak to you.

05:35.293 --> 05:39.088
-Still, don't you have anything to say?
-Are we sleeping in separate rooms?

05:40.715 --> 05:41.924
Depends on you.

05:42.592 --> 05:45.470
There needs to be an excuse for making up.

05:46.971 --> 05:49.640
Okay. Tell me when you're over your anger.

05:50.558 --> 05:52.602
You'll need time to sort out
your emotions.

05:52.977 --> 05:54.270
I won't bother you.

06:01.736 --> 06:02.820
What was that?

06:03.654 --> 06:05.156
He should be holding me.

06:21.255 --> 06:22.298
Just come in.

06:24.258 --> 06:26.177
I was going to go in, out of habit.

06:26.344 --> 06:28.012
My heart isn't in it.

06:28.554 --> 06:30.390
Use this room.
I'll use the smaller room.

06:30.473 --> 06:32.642
No, it's okay. You use it.

06:33.518 --> 06:35.186
My heart isn't at ease about it.

06:37.730 --> 06:39.607
Your heart isn't at ease

06:39.982 --> 06:41.484
and my body will not be at ease.

06:42.110 --> 06:43.152
We'll be the same.

06:51.702 --> 06:53.121
Something is going on.

06:53.955 --> 06:55.164
It's serious.

06:58.167 --> 07:00.670
There are too many things that are off.

07:02.130 --> 07:03.756
He lies all the time.

07:05.675 --> 07:07.969
This is not normal, not at all.

07:23.568 --> 07:24.944
This is dream.

07:25.903 --> 07:28.739
Do you want to be doing house chores
even in your dreams?

07:32.410 --> 07:37.707
This mountain of clothes must represent
my mountain of stress.

07:39.959 --> 07:41.085
Wake up, already.

07:41.627 --> 07:43.838
Wake up!

07:47.300 --> 07:48.176
What is this?

07:51.304 --> 07:54.390
WE MADE HYDROGEN BOMBS

07:54.474 --> 07:57.810
The train will go even if the dog barks?

08:01.522 --> 08:03.858
The capitalist products!

08:05.151 --> 08:06.110
Realtor.

08:07.236 --> 08:08.571
Do not call me that.

08:11.240 --> 08:13.910
Why are you talking like that?

08:15.077 --> 08:16.829
Where was your hometown again?

08:19.040 --> 08:22.251
I am from Pyongyang in
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.

08:22.543 --> 08:24.212
That's nonsense.

08:25.046 --> 08:27.256
How is a North Korean so stylish?

08:31.636 --> 08:32.512
What are you doing?

08:33.554 --> 08:36.140
Spy? Are you a spy?

08:36.224 --> 08:37.642
What are you doing? Oh, my!

08:38.100 --> 08:40.061
You know too much.

08:40.686 --> 08:44.690
-Die quietly for the sake of the homeland.
-No, this is a dream.

08:44.774 --> 08:45.608
Die.

08:45.691 --> 08:47.193
You're dreaming too. Wake up.

08:47.276 --> 08:48.861
-Die.
-Wake up.

08:48.945 --> 08:51.531
Die!

08:51.614 --> 08:52.448
Wake up!

08:52.532 --> 08:55.034
-Die.
-Wake up!

09:01.874 --> 09:05.169
Realtor. I just had a dream about you.

09:06.087 --> 09:07.046
What kind of dream?

09:18.224 --> 09:19.225
No!

09:23.688 --> 09:24.730
What now?

09:26.357 --> 09:27.567
Is this a dream too?

09:29.443 --> 09:30.736
You can't die.

09:31.612 --> 09:32.446
No.

09:39.161 --> 09:40.538
Who dies?

09:41.247 --> 09:42.331
Who's dying?

09:42.415 --> 09:43.291
No.

09:45.418 --> 09:49.463
Hey, it's okay. You can tell me.

09:49.630 --> 09:50.631
Tell me.

09:51.048 --> 09:51.924
What are you doing?

09:53.676 --> 09:54.510
Hey,

09:55.720 --> 09:58.014
why are you blowing into my ear?

09:58.806 --> 10:01.183
You were talking in your sleep,
so I came in.

10:02.018 --> 10:04.312
Why were you talking so much
in your sleep?

10:04.520 --> 10:06.105
What have you been doing?

10:07.106 --> 10:12.028
You don't have to pretend
to be mad like that.

10:53.611 --> 10:55.988
<i>Ma-rin's husband</i>
<i>is your husband's chairman.</i>

10:56.197 --> 10:59.116
<i>A person's life can change so suddenly.</i>

11:18.636 --> 11:21.263
Secretary Hwang, I need to see you now.

11:23.182 --> 11:25.935
You want to know
about Chairman Yu's skeletons?

11:26.644 --> 11:28.896
Everyone has something dirty to hide.

11:29.105 --> 11:30.439
He must have some faults.

11:30.856 --> 11:33.734
I need to know what that is.

11:35.111 --> 11:38.155
Faults? He has several.

11:38.531 --> 11:39.782
-Really?
-Yes.

11:39.865 --> 11:40.866
What are they?

11:41.200 --> 11:43.786
For one thing, he doesn't work hard.

11:43.869 --> 11:46.455
He barely... he doesn't work at all.

11:46.664 --> 11:49.417
Life is a joke,
and work is his playground.

11:49.917 --> 11:51.794
Being rich with lots of time is a fault?

11:52.336 --> 11:53.421
That's attractive.

11:53.963 --> 11:57.133
Ah, I see. It's attractive.

11:57.425 --> 11:59.677
I was being too negative about it.

12:00.177 --> 12:03.889
I've heard that he's mysterious and odd.

12:03.973 --> 12:05.099
He is. Yes.

12:06.976 --> 12:08.060
Let's get straight.

12:08.561 --> 12:11.772
Does he have any issues with other women?

12:12.481 --> 12:15.276
Does he lust after them
or have messy relationships?

12:15.359 --> 12:17.027
Is he a bit of a pervert?

12:18.362 --> 12:19.947
I'm hoping for any of the three.

12:22.950 --> 12:24.577
Relationships with women.

12:25.494 --> 12:26.328
Well...

12:27.413 --> 12:31.417
I don't know
if I should tell you about this.

12:31.500 --> 12:32.334
What is it?

12:33.210 --> 12:38.257
This is so big
that I haven't even told the director.

12:38.340 --> 12:40.259
What is it? You can tell me.

12:40.509 --> 12:41.844
Tell me.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.013
Well, it's just...

12:45.514 --> 12:46.557
It's the chairman's...

12:48.476 --> 12:50.227
sexual identity.

12:53.522 --> 12:55.441
Sexual identity?

12:58.152 --> 13:01.655
I happened to... overhear

13:01.739 --> 13:05.367
the chairman talking to Manager Kang.

13:05.826 --> 13:08.412
Why did you do something
I didn't ask for?

13:08.954 --> 13:11.165
I've always felt

13:11.248 --> 13:14.168
they've had a strange relationship.

13:14.502 --> 13:17.338
It's more than just friendship.

13:17.588 --> 13:20.549
Then I heard the conclusive words.

13:21.050 --> 13:23.302
I've been living at your place.

13:23.636 --> 13:25.012
Think of it as rent.

13:25.721 --> 13:26.931
Living at his place?

13:27.097 --> 13:29.058
I really hate it.

13:30.309 --> 13:32.478
-Come on, Ki-doong.
-Stop!

13:32.561 --> 13:33.479
He's touching him!

13:33.562 --> 13:35.314
-Don't be mad.
-Stop.

13:35.397 --> 13:36.482
Is he getting pouty?

13:37.107 --> 13:39.819
This isn't the kind of smile
a man gives another man.

13:39.902 --> 13:42.530
This is the face men make
when they see girl groups.

13:43.113 --> 13:45.783
<i>-Don't be like that, not between us.</i>
<i>-Oh, you're...</i>

13:45.866 --> 13:47.159
He said "between us".

13:47.243 --> 13:49.578
All right, watch this.

13:49.703 --> 13:51.872
There will be bold touching
on the left side.

13:51.956 --> 13:54.500
Men wouldn't do this
even if they were paid.

13:54.625 --> 13:56.919
Yes, I see that you're right.

13:57.002 --> 13:59.755
They just can't live without each other.

14:00.130 --> 14:02.883
They also share
the chairman's office.

14:03.342 --> 14:06.095
That's unheard of in a company.

14:06.178 --> 14:10.057
They don't care
about what the world thinks.

14:10.140 --> 14:11.308
They're very passionate.

14:11.392 --> 14:14.603
They're burning hot.
They're just flying hot.

14:14.687 --> 14:16.605
They share an office?

14:16.689 --> 14:18.524
-The chairman and a manager?
-Yes.

14:18.607 --> 14:20.067
Watch this part here.

14:20.150 --> 14:23.070
This will confirm it.

14:23.737 --> 14:28.242
<i>Let's meet at your house</i>
<i>on December 3rd this year.</i>

14:29.118 --> 14:30.244
<i>Why?</i>

14:30.327 --> 14:32.329
<i>I want to tell you what it's all about.</i>

14:32.538 --> 14:34.415
<i>I don't want to complicate your life.</i>

14:34.957 --> 14:37.543
<i>But I have something I need to ask you.</i>

14:37.877 --> 14:38.794
That's the end.

14:39.628 --> 14:40.838
What does that mean?

14:41.255 --> 14:43.299
They see each other daily.

14:43.799 --> 14:46.260
Why would they promise to see each other
in December?

14:47.177 --> 14:50.097
I will confess all of my feelings for you
on that day.

14:50.472 --> 14:54.393
Let's meet on that day in December
and make it romantic.

14:55.561 --> 14:59.106
"On December 3, this year...

15:00.274 --> 15:03.235
let's promise to meet at your house."

15:04.361 --> 15:05.446
-Oh, my.
-Oh, my.

15:05.529 --> 15:09.325
-Oh, my! I can't believe it.
-Oh, my.

15:09.742 --> 15:10.868
It's love.

15:11.368 --> 15:14.330
A forbidden and sad love
that can't be spoken of.

15:15.539 --> 15:19.501
I thought it was strange
that he married Bap-soon in a rush.

15:20.252 --> 15:21.921
-A marriage to hide himself?
-Hide...

15:22.171 --> 15:24.340
-His sexual identity... Oh dear.
-Oh my.

15:34.141 --> 15:37.061
No, this is my area.

15:40.773 --> 15:41.732
Go over there.

15:45.986 --> 15:48.614
Hey. Come over here.

15:50.240 --> 15:51.200
Go over there.

15:54.703 --> 15:56.246
Do you understand me?

15:57.623 --> 15:58.457
Stop.

16:05.130 --> 16:08.133
Even the vacuum
in this house is a mystery.

16:20.187 --> 16:21.063
What?

16:23.941 --> 16:24.817
Now?

16:27.945 --> 16:29.196
I sent you a text.

16:29.780 --> 16:32.783
That's Manager Kang's address,
where your husband's been living.

16:32.866 --> 16:33.742
Look into it.

16:35.202 --> 16:38.205
Your husband is cheating.
Who cares if it's with a man or a woman?

16:38.288 --> 16:40.207
You just have to catch him.

16:40.290 --> 16:41.417
Hey, Lee Gun-sook.

16:42.126 --> 16:46.463
What will you do if Chairman Yu
likes men and married you to hide that?

16:46.547 --> 16:50.467
Your life will be totally over.

16:51.635 --> 16:54.096
With women,
at least you can pull their hair out.

16:54.179 --> 16:55.681
How will you beat up a man?

16:56.682 --> 16:59.393
My husband's man.

16:59.727 --> 17:00.602
Hey.

17:02.229 --> 17:03.939
That's harsh. It really is.

17:04.815 --> 17:05.774
You're excited.

17:06.942 --> 17:07.985
You're very excited.

17:08.902 --> 17:11.071
Does time go backward for Lee Gun-sook?

17:11.822 --> 17:13.574
Why do you get more childish?

17:13.657 --> 17:15.784
I'm just saying this out of concern.

17:16.243 --> 17:19.371
-The rumors could get really messy.
-Enough.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.791
I can't take this anymore.

17:24.168 --> 17:27.087
Do you sit around 24 hours a day
thinking how to screw me over?

17:28.088 --> 17:30.466
You don't get paid for it.
Why work so hard at it?

17:31.133 --> 17:32.718
You should get paid for it.

17:34.803 --> 17:37.056
Do you think I'm making this up?

17:38.057 --> 17:40.726
Fine. Believe what you want.

17:44.396 --> 17:45.397
Listen.

17:46.106 --> 17:50.903
If you ran out of fresh ideas, retire now.
Or bring something more innovative.

17:50.986 --> 17:54.156
What could be more innovative than this?

17:54.239 --> 17:56.408
It's a man. Not a woman, a man.

17:56.492 --> 17:58.410
Seriously, stop with the nonsense.

18:00.579 --> 18:02.915
Also, you shouldn't go after my family.

18:03.457 --> 18:06.168
What kind of dirty play is this?

18:09.463 --> 18:10.923
Check your message.

18:12.007 --> 18:13.092
Take a good look.

18:14.551 --> 18:15.636
Go ahead!

18:22.518 --> 18:25.062
What am I doing right now?

18:25.687 --> 18:27.648
Where is 12 Hannam-dong?

18:30.359 --> 18:31.652
Aren't you going home?

18:32.444 --> 18:34.571
You'll be bored having dinner alone.

18:35.072 --> 18:36.532
I'll eat with you and go.

18:36.615 --> 18:39.827
Do you feel scared to go home
and eat dinner now?

18:40.619 --> 18:42.246
Am I the type to be scared?

18:42.704 --> 18:43.747
Whatever.

18:44.873 --> 18:48.919
You can't even go home,
and you're here at your friend's house.

18:49.002 --> 18:50.879
My gosh.

18:51.755 --> 18:54.967
It's so dirty! Go into that corner.

18:55.050 --> 18:57.886
-Help me up.
-Get up now. Hurry.

18:58.554 --> 19:00.848
Seriously, you punk!

19:11.024 --> 19:12.067
You're heavy.

19:13.610 --> 19:14.486
Yes.

19:17.322 --> 19:18.532
I'll rest a bit.

19:19.116 --> 19:20.450
<i>Where are you now?</i>

19:26.790 --> 19:29.376
<i>I'm working. I'll be a bit late today.</i>

19:31.587 --> 19:33.172
Of course, he's at work.

19:33.589 --> 19:34.882
Why would he be here?

19:38.385 --> 19:39.428
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

19:41.388 --> 19:42.347
<i>For what?</i>

19:42.764 --> 19:45.434
<i>I just did something to be sorry for.</i>

19:45.976 --> 19:47.102
<i>It's nothing.</i>

19:50.480 --> 19:51.940
<i>I have so much work to do today.</i>

19:52.441 --> 19:54.985
<i>Still, I am the head of the family.</i>
<i>I'll do my best!</i>

19:55.360 --> 19:56.737
Let's go play pool.

19:56.820 --> 19:58.113
He has lots of work!

19:58.197 --> 19:59.865
-No.
-Why not?

20:00.199 --> 20:02.993
-Internet Cafe.
-Are you a kid?

20:03.076 --> 20:05.746
-Are you an old man, then?
-Let's go and play pool.

20:12.461 --> 20:13.670
Isn't that Ma-rin?

20:16.006 --> 20:17.216
Honey!

20:19.218 --> 20:20.594
What brings you here?

20:20.677 --> 20:22.721
I came by to run some errands.

20:24.514 --> 20:26.099
-Hello.
-Hello.

20:26.183 --> 20:28.060
-It's been a long time.
-Yes.

20:30.020 --> 20:31.647
-Honey.
-Yes.

20:31.730 --> 20:34.733
I'm so shocked! What a small world.

20:34.816 --> 20:36.985
Aren't you cold? No?

20:37.069 --> 20:38.820
I don't think this was a coincidence.

20:39.780 --> 20:40.656
What wasn't?

20:42.074 --> 20:43.992
-What?
-What wasn't?

20:44.076 --> 20:45.077
It's not that.

20:45.160 --> 20:49.957
We met by coincidence. I'll get going now.

20:52.084 --> 20:53.085
Hey!

21:02.886 --> 21:05.764
Did you follow me or something? Why?

21:06.139 --> 21:07.349
You said you were at work.

21:08.684 --> 21:11.103
You must be working at Ki-doong's house.

21:11.561 --> 21:13.563
Oh, that...

21:15.315 --> 21:16.525
Are you dating Ki-doong?

21:17.484 --> 21:18.318
What?

21:19.236 --> 21:22.364
